data.name: text
data.value: Pieces walnut generally refers to the walnut kernel that has been removed from the outer shell, meaning it is devoid of the shell and inner membranes. These inner walnut kernels, separated from their shells, are often found in broken or chopped form. This makes it easier to consume the inner walnut. Broken walnuts can be used in salads, meals, desserts, or snacks.

data.name: text1
data.value: Walnuts contain nutrients that provide many health benefits, so consuming broken walnuts contributes to the intake of nutrients such as omega-3 fatty acids, antioxidants, vitamins, and minerals. Broken walnuts, in particular, serve as a source of alpha-linolenic acid (ALA), which is an omega-3 fatty acid. Omega-3 fatty acids can offer various health benefits, including supporting brain health, heart health, and combating inflammation. Walnuts are rich in antioxidants. Antioxidants can protect the body against the harmful effects of free radicals and reduce cellular damage.

data.name: text2
data.value: Walnuts contribute to weight control due to their filling properties. By helping you feel full for a longer time, they contribute to reducing the risk of overeating. Fiber is an ingredient that contributes to digestive health and provides a sense of fullness. Walnuts are rich in fiber. They also serve as a plant-based protein source. Protein is essential for the repair of body tissues, muscle development, and various other biological processes.

data.name: text2.5
data.value: The vitamins, minerals, and antioxidants found in walnuts support skin health and reduce signs of aging. Walnuts contain omega-3 fatty acids, antioxidants, and other nutrients that support heart health. Thanks to these properties, they can improve cardiovascular health.

data.name: text3
data.value: LİGHT AMBER walnut is a high-quality product collected from walnut trees grown in the Kahramanmaraş province of Turkey. The unique taste and aroma characteristics of Maraş18 butterfly walnut are shaped by the geographical conditions in this region. Its thin-shell and large inner structure win the approval of even the most discerning palates. However, Maraş18 butterfly walnut stands out not only for its taste but also for its health benefits.

data.name: text3.5
data.value: Rich in omega-3 fatty acids, antioxidants, vitamin E, magnesium, and other nutrients, Maraş18 butterfly walnut is beneficial for brain health and mental functions. Research indicates that regular consumption of these nutrients may contribute to the renewal of brain cells and the improvement of brain functions. Additionally, Maraş18 butterfly walnut can help reduce the risk of various diseases such as heart health, diabetes, cancer, and more. It is used in many different recipes, ranging from savory dishes to desserts. It can be consumed either roasted or raw.

data.name: text5
data.value: AMBER walnut, belonging to the Juglans regia species, is a type of walnut. The Persian walnut tree is typically large and long-lived, with large, compound leaves that have serrated edges. The fruit of the Persian walnut is generally large and has a tough shell. The shell may have colors ranging from light brown to reddish. The inner part of the Persian walnut, especially in some subspecies of Juglans regia, contains a rich flavor and oil. It is a highly nutritious and energizing snack. Persian walnuts grow in temperate climates and can be found in a wide geographical area. This type is often cultivated in forested areas in Asia, Europe, and North America.

data.name: text5.5
data.value: Walnuts are rich in omega-3 fatty acids, antioxidants, protein, and fiber, making them a healthy food source. Some research suggests that regularly consuming walnuts can support heart health and provide other health benefits. The shell of Persian walnuts typically has color tones ranging between brown and reddish, which is particularly pronounced in mature walnuts and serves as a distinguishing feature from other walnut varieties. The inner part of the Persian walnut, especially in specific subspecies, carries an intense flavor and distinctive aroma, making it a characteristic that sets it apart from other walnut types.
